From 37c874a77404a348107d94b0024ed1ac6ac734b0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sebastian Bresin <sebastian.bresin@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Feb 2026 13:21:03 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] feat: add leadingspacewidth auto-computation plugin

Add runtime/plugin/leadingspacewidth.lua that automatically computes
and sets 'leadingspacewidth' based on tabstop and shiftwidth for
space-indented buffers. Opt-in via vim.g.leadingspacewidth_auto = true.

Formula: lsw = tabstop / shiftwidth (when expandtab is set and tabstop
is evenly divisible by shiftwidth). If lsw would be 1 (no visual
expansion), lsw is set to 0 (disabled).

Fires on BufReadPost (after editorconfig/ftplugin have set indent
options) and on OptionSet for shiftwidth/expandtab/tabstop to react
to mid-session changes (e.g. vim-sleuth re-detecting on FileType).

Per-buffer override via vim.b.leadingspacewidth_auto = false.
Compatible with EditorConfig, vim-sleuth, guess-indent.nvim, and
any plugin that sets shiftwidth + expandtab.

12 functional tests covering auto-computation, OptionSet reactivity,
per-buffer disable, and editorconfig integration.
